The Chronicle Pamela Shumba, Senior Reporter Patron of the environmental clean up campaign First Lady Amai Auxilia Mnangagwa is in Bulawayo for a clean up exercise in the city. The First Lady is being accompanied by Bulawayo provincial Minister Judith Ncube and Environment, Tourism and Hospitality Industry Minister Prisca Mupfumira. Officials from the Bulawayo City Council, EMA, , ZRP , ZPCS, various Government departments,other organisations and schools are gathered at Pick and Pay in the city Centre in support of the campaign. Different groups of people will be allocated different places where they will clean. The First Friday of every month has been set aside as a day to clean up cities. Zanu-PF Politburo and Central Committee members , Hospitals and Funeral Palours are also part of the campaign